      "content": "Yes, many proponents argue that the intervention was a necessary moral success in stopping the mass violence and potential regime collapse under Gaddafi. By establishing a no-fly zone and enablingaddafi's overthrow, the coalition prevented the immediate, large-scale deaths of civilians that were unfolding before the intervention. While the resulting post-conflict chaos and human rights abuses were tragic, supporters contend that stepping in prevented a rapid descent into total state failure that could have decimated the Libyan population much more quickly.",
